{{NCAATeamFootballSeason |Year=1898 |Team=Drake Bulldogs |Image= |Conference=Independent |ShortConference= |Division= |CoachRank= |APRank= |BCSRank= |Record= 4&ndash;2 |ConfRecord= |HeadCoach= [[A. B. Potter]] |OffCoach= |DefCoach= |OScheme= |DScheme= |StadiumArena=[[Haskins Field]] |Champion= |BowlTourney= |BowlTourneyResult= }} The '''1898 Drake Bulldogs football team''' represented [[Drake University]] during the [[1898 college football season]]. It was the sixth year for the football program. The season ended with an 4&ndash;2 record, Drake's first winning season. The Bulldogs concluded the season with a 6&ndash;5 win [[1898 Nebraska Bugeaters football team|Nebraska]], crowning them as the best team in the west for 1898.
